This paper deals with the list-decoding problem of alternant codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of the decoding radius, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a complexity analysis of the algorithm, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
